CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 20, 1957, pg. 28 reads: "Three Parking Violators - This "NO PARKING AT ANY TIME" sign at the corner of Wylie Ave. and Fullerton St. is abused day and hight by motorists, who not only ignore it, but also insist on parking too close to the corner like this photograph shows. Oftimes, street cars ,attempting to make the left turn off Wylie Ave. to Fullerton St. have troubled getting by the parked vehicles, because the rear end of the street car is unable to swing around the required clearance, which is clearly marked by a painted line...Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Wylie Avenue with Goode Pharmacy, Stanley's Shoe Shine and Billiards, and Pharmacist William Goode's grey and white Buick car parked in center, near Fullerton Avenue, Hill District
